      conclusion: "The fear of God's interruption is really a fear that God's plan will be worse than yours. Paul's story, C.S. Lewis's story, and ultimately Jesus' own life (the most interrupted human story in history) are God's answer to that fear. God's plan for you is not a consolation prize. It is the purpose you were made for.",
