      obedienceLink: "Sanctification is the deep structure of obedience. Obedience commanded by external law produces constraint and resentment. Obedience produced by interior transformation — by the Spirit writing the law on the heart — is the fulfilment of Jeremiah 31:33 and Ezekiel 36:27. John 15:14 — 'ye are my friends, if ye do whatsoever I command you' — is not a condition of affection but a description of a transformed relationship. Friends want to do what their friend loves. Sanctification is the Spirit producing in the believer a wanting to obey that replaces the straining to obey. The goal of all spiritual growth is obedience that feels like home.",
